(1, 1, '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Hello world!', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world__trashed', '', '', '2022-06-10 18:14:20', '2022-06-10 18:14:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost/velikiproj/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(2, 1, '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Node.js je veoma popularno izvršno okruženje za JavaScript. Node.js je prirode otvorenog izvora, a takođe je i kompatibilan sa velikim spektrom operativnih sistema, što ga i čini veoma popularnim među “backend” programerima .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ugrubo rečeno Node.js je program koji izvršrava JavaScript na serverskoj strani, u odnosu na standardno korisničko izvršavanje u okviru web pretraživača. Samim tim obrada podataka je mnogo brža ( ako računamo da je server na kom je Node.js pokrenut dovoljno jak, moćan) nego kod običnog izvršavanja JavaScript koda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Gdje se Node.js najčešće koristi:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Node.js se najčešće koristi u mrežnim aplikacijama gdje je potrebna komunikacija u realnom vremenu između dva krajnja mrežna čvora.&nbsp; Za razliku od PHP izvršavanje funkcija u JS nije serijski (sljedeća komanda se izvršava tek kada se trenutna komanda završi), već su dizajnirane da se izvršavaju paralelno, što već teorijski pruža dosta manja vremena u obradi podataka.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Takođe Node.js serverima donosi paradigmu programiranja vođenja događajima, u kom se komande izvršavaju kada se izvrše određeni definisani događaji. Upravo zbog ove paradigme Node.js omogućava programeru da napravi visoko proširiv server koji je u mogućnosti da podnese protok podataka koji je u mogućnosti da raste veoma brzo u kratkom vremenskom roku tako što se koristi dosta pojednostavljeniji model programiranja vođenja događajima koje koristi funkcijsko „poziv poslije“ da označi završetak ili neuspjeh izvršavanja zadatka, i to bez koriščenja „threading-a“.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Trenutno najčešća upotreba Node.js je u MEAN (MongoDB, Express.js, Angular i Node.js) za kreiranje i razvoj visoko kvalitetnih dinamičkih sajtova i aplikacija. Takođe se i koristi u Electronu (poseban okvir za računarske GKI programe poput Visual Studio Code, Atom, Skype itd...)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Istorija Node.js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Programer Rajen Dal je 2009 godine je napisao Node.js, koji je u početku samo podržavao Linux i Mac OS X operativne sisteme. Okruženje je kombinovalo Google-ov V8 JS pogon, sistem ciklusa događaja i ulazno/izlazni API na niskom nivou.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nepunih godinu dana kasnije uveden je npm (Node Package Manager) koji je odličan za raspolaganje korisnički kreiranih kodnih paketa otvorenog izvora. Pomoću npm-a korisnik može da dijeli, ažurira, instalira i deinstalira razne pakete.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Juna 2011. godine Microsoft I Joynet su napravili i izbacili Windows verziju Node.js.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Januara 2012 godine Dahl napušta i unapređuje Izaka Šultera (koji je razvio npm) u poziciju upravljanja Node.js-a . Januara 2014 Šulter je najavio da vođstvo projekta preuzima Timoti J. Fontejn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Decembra 2014. godine Zbog unutrašnjeg konflikta u Joynetovom upravljanju, Fedor Indutnji je kreirao io.js koji je alternative otvorenog upravljanja. Jedan od glavnih ciljeva je da se dođe do verzije 1.0 što brže moguće. Juna 2015. zajednice io.js I Node.js su se složili da rade zajedno pod “Node.js Foundation”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Septembra 2015. godine verzije 0.12 I 3.3 Node.js-a su spojene u Node v4.0. Ovim spajanjem su ubačene ES6 mogućnosti u Node.js i uz to je Node.js ušao u ciklus dugoročnih ažuriranja.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tek 2019. Godine JS Foundation i Node.js Foundation su se spojili kako bi formirali OpenJS Foundation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Instalacija Node.js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kako bismo instalirali Node.js prvo što je potrebno uraditi jeste da odemo na stranicu za preuzimanje Node.JS, a to jeste <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://nodejs.org/en/download/</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Za sisteme sa Windows familijom operativnih sistemoa preuzmemo msi paket za automatsko instaliranje u sistem ili zip paket radi ručne instalacije.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Za sisteme sa macOS familijom operativnih sistema preuzmemo pkg paket za automatsko instaliranje u sistem ili tar.gz paket radi ručne instalacije.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Za Linux-zasnovane distribucije Node.JS možemo instalirati preko raznih upravljača paketa (Pacman, apt, portage, yum), ili preuzmemo već kompajlan program u zavisnosti arhitekture procesora koja je zastupljena u računaru (ARM, x86_64, s390x).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Takođe možemo sami kompajlati izvorni kod i tako stvoriti potpuno funkcionalan program Node.JS-a (<a href=\"https://github.com/nodejs/node\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://github.com/nodejs/node</a>).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Pokretanje i korišćenje Node.js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pokretanje Node.js je veoma lagano, prvo što uradimo jeste da otvorimo komandu liniju operativnog sistema (CMD, Terminal, PowerShell,itd.), zatim u komandnu liniju upišemo <code>node</code> i potvrdimo unos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kada potvrdimo unos, bićemo pozdravljeni sa Node.JS REPL-om</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>~&gt;node\nWelcome to Node.js v17.3.0.\nType .help for more information.\n&gt;_</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>REPL nam omogućava unos Node.js i JavaScript komandi i praćenje odgovarajućih događaja u samoj node aplikaciji. Kako bismo pokrenuli Node aplikaciju, potrebno je ukucati <code><strong>.load &lt;ime_aplikacije.js></strong></code> (aplikacija mora biti u istom folderu u kom je otvoren i node) i potvrditi unos. Takođe aplikaciju možemo otvoriti direkto u komandnoj liniji, tako što preko komande linije dođemo do lokacije gdje se nalazi node aplikacija, pa u komandnu liniju ukucamo <strong><code>node &lt;ime_aplikacije.js></code> </strong>i potvrdimo unos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Takođe imamo sljedeće komande:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong><code>.save</code> </strong>– za argument uzima ime datoteke u kojoj želimo da spremimo trenutnu REPL sesiju;</li><li><code><strong>.editor</strong> </code>– omogućava višelinijski unos JavaScript koda;</li><li><code><strong>.break</strong></code> – radi isto što i Ctrl-C, a to jeste prekida trenutno izvršavanje programa;</li><li><strong><code>.exit</code> </strong>– izlazi iz REPL, alternativa za 2x Ctrl-C ili Ctrl-D (EOF); </li><li><code><strong>.help</strong> </code>– prikazuje komande i opis tih istih komandi.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Možemo prikazati neki izlaz na REPL pomoću console.log metode, npr:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt; console.log(\"Zdravo svijete!\")\nZdravo svijete!</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->\n\n<!-- wp:themify-builder/canvas /-->', 'Uvod/O Node.js', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'uvod', '', '', '2022-06-10 21:07:50', '2022-06-10 21:07:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/velikiproj/?page_id=2', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(3, 1, '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '2022-06-10 10:25:03', '<!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we are</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Our website address is: http://localhost/velikiproj.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Comments</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Media</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Cookies</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Embedded content from other websites</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Where your data is sent</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p><strong class=\"privacy-policy-tutorial\">Suggested text: </strong>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'open', '', 'privacy-policy__trashed', '', '', '2022-06-10 19:59:51', '2022-06-10 19:59:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost/velikiproj/?page_id=3', 0, 'page', '', 0),
